summary: This is an email chain from June 10, 2020, between a Senior Financial Investigator and an Assistant U.S. Attorney regarding missing subpoena returns in the Epstein investigation. The emails discuss subpoenas served on state and territorial corporate divisions to obtain records for entities like NAUTILUS, INC. and LSJ LLC.

keyFacts: Investigators were actively pursuing corporate records related to Epstein as of June 2020.
Subpoenas were issued in 2019 to multiple state and territorial corporate divisions (Albany, USVI, Delaware).
The entities of interest included NAUTILUS, INC. and LSJ LLC.
The email chain indicates missing returns for these subpoenas, prompting follow-up.
The correspondence involves a Senior Financial Investigator from Squad C-40 (FAST) and an Assistant U.S. Attorney from the Southern District of New York.
